    <div class="content-section">
        <h2>1. Old City</h2>
        <p>The Old City (İçərişəhər) is an ancient residential quarter - historical and architectural reserve in the capital of Azerbaijan, Baku. Surrounded by well-preserved fortress walls, it is the most ancient part and landmark of the city. The most significant architectural monuments in Icheri-sheher are the Maiden Tower and the complex of Shirvanshahs Palace. In addition, dozens of historical monuments - mosques, caravanserais, bathhouses, residential houses, several museums, embassies, hotels, shopping facilities, cafes, and restaurants are located on the territory of the reserve.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
        <img src="old city 1.jpg" alt="Baku" class="move-lower" width="400" height="300">
    </div>
    <h2>2. Shirvanshahs Palace</h2>
<p>
    Shirvanshahs' Palace (Şirvanşahlar sarayı) is the former residence of the Shirvanshahs.
    It forms a complex, which besides the palace itself also includes the courtyard of the Divan-Khane, the tomb of the Shirvanshahs, the palace mosque of 1441, the bathhouse and the mausoleum of the court scholar Seyyid Yahya Bakuvi. The construction of the palace was connected with the transfer of the capital of the Shirvanshahs' state from Shemakha to Baku. In 2000, the unique architectural and cultural ensemble, along with the walled historic part of the city and the Maiden Tower, was included in the UNESCO World Heritage List. The Shirvanshahs' Palace is still considered one of the pearls of Azerbaijani architecture today
</p>
<img src="ширван ночь.jpeg" alt="center" width="400" height="200">
<img src="ширван.jpeg" alt="center" width="400" height="200">
<h2>3. Maiden Tower</h2>
<p>
    Maiden Tower (Qız Qalası) is an ancient fortress building near the coastal part of Icheri-Sheher. It is one of the most important components of the seaside “facade” of Baku. The tower stands on a rock, its height is 28 meters above sea level. The tower is included in the UNESCO World Heritage List. There are many legends around the Maiden Tower, all of which are very interesting.
</p>
<img src="qizqalasi.jpg" alt="center" width="350" height="350">
<img src="qiz 2.jpg" alt="center" width="450" height="350">
