<h2>4. Heydar Aliev Centre</h2>
<p>
    Heydar Aliyev Center (Heydər Əliyev Mərkəzi) is a cultural center located on Heydar Aliyev Avenue in Baku, 
    the capital of Azerbaijan. The center is a complex building that includes an auditorium, museum, exhibition 
    halls and administrative offices.
    The center was designed in 2007 by architect Zaha Hadid. The Heydar Aliyev Cultural Center is considered one 
    of the symbols of modern Baku.
</p>
<img src="Гейдар снаружи.jpg" alt="center" width="300" height="300"> <img src="Гейдар изнутри.jpg" alt="centre" width="300" height="300">
